(making her more nervous
than before the show.)

52
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:24,680
Alright.

53
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,080
Here, two slices of meat.

54
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:27,160
Okay.

55
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,520
Shredded pork noodles.

56
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:30,680
Eat as much as you want today.

57
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:32,200
Master Song,

58
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:34,760
your kitchen has hidden talents.

59
00:03:34,760 --> 00:03:36,720
You really wowed us today.

60
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:37,600
You deserve praise.

61
00:03:37,770 --> 00:03:38,640
You deserve praise.

62
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:39,640
You bet.

63
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:41,680
People always look down on us,

64
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:43,320
complaining about taste

65
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:44,760
and anything else.

66
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,040
Look at you guys.

67
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:46,920
Which one of you

68
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,320
is better than our kitchen maid?

69
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:49,560
Look at you.

70
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:51,040
Look how arrogant you are.

71
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:52,640
Arrogant? I'm being modest now.

72
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,960
Modest? Come on.

73
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:56,080
If anyone complains
about our cooking again,

74
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,120
you can do the cooking,

75
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,360
and we'll go perform on stage.

76
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,160
- Deal!
- I'm so proud!

77
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:02,440
- I'm starving!
- Come on!

78
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,120
Eat up. It's really good.

79
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:07,920
Why aren't those girls eating?

80
00:04:08,510 --> 00:04:10,340
Girls are just complicated.

81
00:04:10,340 --> 00:04:11,280
Hurry up! Come on over!

82
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:12,280
- Here.
- More meat.

83
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,520
Can I have a second bowl?

84
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:17,120
Why are you all just sitting here?

85
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:18,680
Aren't you getting food?

86
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:20,960
These noodles are really good.

87
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,160
Shredded pork.

88
00:04:28,290 --> 00:04:29,300
Brat.

89
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:30,600
Why is he so annoying?

90
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,920
You always looked down on her.

91
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:34,680
Now, she's a success.

92
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,080
Are you jealous?

93
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,240
What? Are you fine with it?

94
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,960
We wasted all these years.

95
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:42,680
So what?

96
00:04:42,960 --> 00:04:44,200
Should I act like you guys?

97
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,240
Do I have to cry about it?

98
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,400
Listen.

99
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,160
She's suffered so much over the years.

100
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:51,080
Do you even know? Seriously.

101
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:52,720
She just got lucky.

102
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,400
Right. She got lucky.

103
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:58,340
Would you trade your life for hers?

104
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,200
Would you?

105
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,760
You little suck-up.

106
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,120
What's it got to do with you?

107
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:03,520
She's insulting me.

108
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,000
Listen to me.

109
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,360
Every single one of you.

110
00:05:06,960 --> 00:05:08,640
You have one thing, eyeing another.

111
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,040
You want rice and noodles too.

112
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:12,160
You can't eat all the delicacies.

113
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,000
Exactly.

114
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,800
You can't take every good thing.

115
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:15,680
That's right.

116
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,560
Try to let it go.

117
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,440
Let it go, okay?

118
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:20,840
What's it to you if she succeeded?

119
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,840
Why are you so excited?

120
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:23,760
Exactly.

121
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:27,120
These noodles lack vinegar.

122
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:29,000
Not sour enough. I'll add some vinegar.

123
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,000
- Eat up.
- Yeah.

124
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,160
Eat yourselves to death.

125
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:33,160
I hope you choke.

126
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,760
I'd gladly choke on shredded pork.

127
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:37,960
Celebration banquet!

128
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,520
Pour it. Pour some more.

129
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:41,360
Let's celebrate.

130
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,240
Cheers!

131
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,800
- Come on.
- Okay, pour it.

132
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:45,880
Kid,

133
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,000
today

134
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,720
was the best drink

135
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:53,720
I've had in a long time

136
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:59,640
and the best show I've seen.

137
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,000
Kid,

138
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,680
pour Mr. Qin some wine.

139
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:07,360
- No, no.
- A toast to Mr. Qin.

140
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,480
No, no.

141
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:09,640
Without Mr. Qin,

142
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,440
you'd have no debut performance today.

143
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,840
All right. I wouldn't dare.

144
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:15,320
- Easy.
- Fill it up.

145
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:16,200
Just a little. Good.

146
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:17,710
- Fill it.
- What little?

147
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,760
Oh, kid,

148
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:21,560
you should toast all your masters.

149
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,000
They

150
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:26,600
taught you real skills

151
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:29,600
to make your own way.

152
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,480
And, kid,

153
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:35,280
thank your uncle most of all.

154
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:40,240
He's the one who changed your life.

155
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,360
Too bad he isn't here.

156
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,480
Kid,

157
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:46,240
drink this chicken soup.

158
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:49,280
I heard you fainted
after leaving the stage.

159
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,640
Drink this to nurture yourself.

160
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:51,920
- I was worried.
- Come on.

161
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:52,950
- Thanks, Aunt.
- Drink.

162
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:54,320
- But I still feel sick.
- Drink.

163
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,400
I'm afraid I'll throw up.

164
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:57,040
She's not feeling well.
She just fainted.

165
00:06:57,306 --> 00:06:58,366
Why not just keep it warm?

166
00:06:58,377 --> 00:06:59,815
She'll ask for it when she needs it.

167
00:06:59,826 --> 00:07:01,960
Okay, I'll keep it warm in the pot.

168
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,800
If you want it later, just drink up.

169
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,760
Thanks, Aunt.

170
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,440
It's nothing. Sit down.

171
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,680
Sit down. Look at you.

172
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:13,760
Master Gou, I have to head back.

173
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,000
Where are you going?

174
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,560
I'm heading back to help
Master Song clean up.

175
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,880
No need. Stay here.

176
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,840
Today, you're an actress.

177
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:24,440
Right.

178
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:25,880
Sit here.

179
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,640
Aunt Mi Lan.

180
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,720
Aunt Mi Lan.

181
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,800
Why are you crying?

182
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,760
When did you learn opera
from Master Gou?

183
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,800
Since I was little.

184
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,360
Have you been practicing

185
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,200
all these years?

186
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,213
I haven't skipped a single day.

187
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:38,600
Master Gou

188
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,600
wouldn't even let me go home.

189
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,640
And I had no idea.

190
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,760
Master Gou wouldn't let me tell anyone.

191
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,920
You had enough on your plate back then.

192
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:59,280
You grew up in the blink of an eye.

193
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,800
I feel like I barely know you.

194
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,960
My head is still spinning.

195
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,840
I knew nothing.

196
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:10,040
I was unprepared,

197
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:11,940
and Master Gou and the guys
pushed me on stage.

198
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:14,560
I was just confused too.

199
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:16,080
You'd been preparing all along.

200
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,600
You just didn't know it.

201
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,920
Today, when I saw you onstage,

202
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:33,520
I was happy for you.

203
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:37,120
I felt sorry for myself.

204
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,920
It was hard enough
to outlast Hua Caixiang.

205
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,640
Now, you've grown up too.

206
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:48,920
I could still compete with Hua Caixiang.

207
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:53,040
But with you, I never had a chance.

208
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,480
Still, I have to thank you.

209
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,880
Now, I know

210
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:15,440
what to do next.

211
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,000
Aunt Mi Lan.

212
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:20,440
Don't call me Aunt.

213
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:24,920
I'm not that old. Call me Sis.

214
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,640
I'm so jealous of you.

215
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:40,680
After all these years of work,

216
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,200
I still couldn't do it,

217
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:46,760
but you went onstage
and became the lead.

218
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,880
I don't want the lead.

219
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,200
Why?

220
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,200
I never wanted it since I was a kid.

221
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:58,480
I'm scared.

222
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:00,160
Scared of what?

223
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,680
I'm scared of standing on stage.

224
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:08,720
What were all these years

225
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,640
of hard work and suffering for?

226
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:13,000
He didn't want me to give up.

227
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,360
Who is he?

228
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:18,480
My uncle.

229
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,440
What are you doing? What's wrong?

230
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,520
Let's learn from Meng Liang

231
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:01,360
and Jiao Zan.

232
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,120
Who are Meng Liang and Jiao Zan?

233
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:05,120
Master Qiu and Master Zhou.

234
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:07,880
Are you nuts?
It's the middle of the night!

235
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,240
Give me the blanket.

236
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:12,880
Don't sleep! Get up and chat.

237
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:13,960
I can't sleep.

238
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,600
Go talk to Chu Jiahe.

239
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,440
Right now,

240
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,880
she's probably awake too.

241
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,320
I'm going home to tell my mom

242
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:31,480
that I'm done with it.

243
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,840
I'll take over her job.

244
00:12:33,490 --> 00:12:36,000
Then, all these years go to waste.

245
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:38,360
So what?

246
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,440
Anything's fine.

247
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:40,800
What else can I do?

248
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,240
How did she make it?

249
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,520
I might as well quit too.

250
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:47,760
I'll go back.

251
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,120
All of it was pointless anyway.

252
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,520
It's so unfair.

253
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,040
If someone taught us,

254
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:57,600
we'd act way better than her.

255
00:12:57,920 --> 00:12:58,760
Exactly.

256
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,720
She stole all the spotlight.

257
00:13:04,920 --> 00:13:07,360
Always playing the accordion.

258
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,600
Can he play anything besides this?

259
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:11,640
That's all he's got.

260
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:29,080
So annoying.

261
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:31,000
Can you keep it down?

262
00:13:31,480 --> 00:13:33,240
Idiot, get lost!

263
00:14:17,060 --> 00:14:19,890
♪On the banyan tree by the pond♪

264
00:14:19,890 --> 00:14:23,640
♪Cicadas are singing of summer♪

265
00:14:25,340 --> 00:14:28,080
♪On the swing by the playground♪

266
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:31,920
♪Only butterflies rest upon it♪

267
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:35,950
♪The teacher's chalk on the board♪

268
00:14:35,950 --> 00:14:38,130
♪Is still chirping away endlessly♪

269
00:14:38,130 --> 00:14:40,190
♪Going on and on♪

270
00:14:41,350 --> 00:14:45,480
♪Waiting for class and school to end♪

271
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:48,400
♪Waiting for games in childhood♪

272
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,400
Clothes matter to people.

273
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,680
The girl returns to the kitchen

274
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:06,000
and becomes a kitchen maid again.

275
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:12,640
That's not right.

276
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:13,600
What's wrong?

277
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:16,040
Didn't they say

278
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:17,240
the kid

279
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,760
would move to the trainee class?

280
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,080
Why's there still no word?

281
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,640
Exactly.

282
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:23,760
I even told her she'd marry the stage.

283
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,600
This whole lot.

284
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:29,280
Won't they give her a trick
and drop her?

285
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,680
Yi Qing'e! Yi Qing'e!

286
00:15:34,373 --> 00:15:35,360
Why aren't you training?

287
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:36,280
Why wash veg here?

288
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:37,120
Yeah.

289
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:40,120
You know what?

290
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:42,560
You were amazing on stage last time.

291
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:44,240
We were both stunned watching you.

292
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:45,160
It was impressive.

293
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:46,560
That leg lift of yours

294
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,470
totally wowed the audience.

295
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:50,480
Let me tell you.

296
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,520
You're way better

297
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:53,240
than those girls who just talk big.

298
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,800
You're much better. I'm telling you.

299
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,720
You have such a big basin.

300
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:57,973
Can you finish all that?

301
00:15:57,984 --> 00:15:59,240
Feng Xiaoxiao, give her a hand.

302
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,080
Don't let her...

303
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:01,900
- You should help out too.
- No need.

304
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:02,800
Let me help.

305
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:03,840
- No need.
- It's okay.

306
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:04,920
- Put it down.
- It's fine.

307
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:06,430
- It's okay.
- Just leave it there.

308
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:07,990
- It's fine.
- No need.

309
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:09,680
Don't touch it.

310
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:11,360
Okay, okay, I won't.

311
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:17,440
Well.

312
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:21,000
We want to talk to you about something.

313
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:24,160
We want to ask if your masters

314
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,240
are taking apprentices.

315
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:27,080
We both want to learn opera together.

316
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,920
Yeah, we want to become apprentices too.

317
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:32,240
Please do us a favor.

318
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:33,840
Put in a good word for us.

319
00:16:34,210 --> 00:16:35,080
Yeah.

320
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:37,480
How about this? We'll call you Senior.

321
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:38,320
Right.

322
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:39,440
Senior.

323
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,040
Senior, you...

324
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:42,440
Senior.

325
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:44,480
Help us out, Senior.

326
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:46,560
Senior what? Senior?

327
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,840
Look how smug you are.

328
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:52,640
Let's go.

329
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,200
We'll go ourselves.

330
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,680
On the troupe's rural tour,

331
00:17:14,120 --> 00:17:15,960
the kid really made us proud.

332
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:18,200
Even those snobs

333
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:21,400
praised Cunjia Troupe behind our backs.

334
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:24,680
Four old men and one kid

335
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:29,520
brought the troupe back to life.

336
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:30,960
Amazing.

337
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,640
What's so amazing about that?

338
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:34,080
You think that was a compliment?

339
00:17:34,840 --> 00:17:35,920
From now on, Cunjia Troupe

340
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:37,360
can't be thrown around.

341
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,200
What's wrong?

342
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:40,760
What did we do? Why can't we say it?

343
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,440
I can't control what they say;

344
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:45,360
I can only control what they eat.

345
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:50,040
Why isn't Zhu Jiru around?

346
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,800
He's been back for days.

347
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,120
What happens next?

348
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:56,080
He owes us an explanation.

349
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:57,560
Zhu Jiru?

350
00:17:57,920 --> 00:17:59,720
Even Huang Zhengjing is missing.

351
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:03,920
What are you two looking at?

352
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:05,720
Move along, move along.

353
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,080
Masters above,

354
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:13,720
please accept this from your apprentice.

355
00:18:14,440 --> 00:18:15,520
What's this? What's this?

356
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:16,960
Get up, get up.

357
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:18,720
We want to learn from you.

358
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,440
Please take us in.

359
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:22,400
What are you doing?

360
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,280
Move, move.

361
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:24,640
If you don't agree,

362
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:25,920
we won't get up.

363
00:18:26,850 --> 00:18:27,960
You two little brats.

364
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:29,360
Let's see if you get up.

365
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:31,160
Let's see.

366
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,360
Let's see if you get up.

367
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:34,080
You can take Yi Qing'e.

368
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:35,680
- Why refuse us?
- Exactly.

369
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:37,600
This is a modern troupe,

370
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,000
not an old-style opera troupe.

371
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:40,120
No need for formal vows.

372
00:18:40,120 --> 00:18:41,160
Go on back home.

373
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:43,520
We even kowtowed.

374
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:46,280
That's another matter. Go.

375
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:48,080
How is that different?

376
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:50,080
You only take girls

377
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:51,080
and not boys?

378
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:52,400
Exactly.

379
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:55,480
Listen to yourself.

380
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:56,920
What nonsense are you spouting?

381
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,560
I'll make you pay. I swear.

382
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:02,800
I already told you.

383
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:04,600
Bowing like that won't work.

384
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:07,600
It's all because of you.

385
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,640
Why bring up girls?

386
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:11,800
She's our senior.
I was trying to be friendly.

387
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:12,920
Look at this.

388
00:19:25,120 --> 00:19:25,960
What are you doing?

389
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:27,800
With moves like that,

390
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,080
you might as well go to sleep.

391
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:31,360
Hurry up and train. Move.

392
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:32,280
We'll train.

393
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:33,720
Get moving. Keep training.

394
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:44,800
Where are the girls?

395
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,160
They must be sleeping.

396
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,360
Sleeping?

397
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:51,400
Feng Xiaoxiao.

398
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:53,560
What's going on?

399
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:54,560
I don't know.

400
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:55,800
Go call them.

401
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,000
They won't listen to me.

402
00:19:58,200 --> 00:19:59,360
What can you even do?

403
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:02,120
What are you doing?

404
00:20:03,360 --> 00:20:04,600
I can't take long shots.

405
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,080
You can't catch anything.

406
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:07,400
You're done for.

407
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:08,880
Look at you.

408
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:12,800
Open the door.

409
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,040
- Hurry!
- Coming, sir.

410
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:15,880
Hurry, hurry!

411
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:20,720
What are you doing?

412
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,160
Why take so long to open up?

413
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:28,040
Look at the time. You have to train.

414
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:30,120
Move it. To the training ground.

415
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:32,480
Mr. He,

416
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:34,520
I'm not feeling well today.

417
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,360
I can't train.

418
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:41,080
The rest of you, go now.

419
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:42,040
Mr. He,

420
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:44,000
I'm not feeling well either.

421
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:47,840
Mr. He, I'm not up to it either.

422
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:51,280
What a coincidence.

423
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:54,080
Your cycles all lined up, huh?

424
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:56,200
Fine. Fine.

425
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:58,160
Don't you dare get up.

426
00:20:58,480 --> 00:21:00,640
Stay down. Rest up nice and easy.

427
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:02,560
Just you wait.

428
00:21:12,560 --> 00:21:13,400
Jiahe,

429
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:14,680
what do we do now?

430
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:17,400
Whoever wants to go can go.

431
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:18,920
I'm not going anyway.

432
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:20,600
I'm not going either.

433
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:22,040
Me neither.

434
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:31,720
Troupe Leader! Troupe Leader!

435
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:34,640
Troupe Leader!

436
00:21:36,150 --> 00:21:37,120
You're finally back.

437
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:38,560
We've been back for days.

438
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:39,840
Where have you been?

439
00:21:40,840 --> 00:21:43,240
I had something to handle.
I wasn't with the troupe.

440
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,080
What's up?

441
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,480
I wanted to brief you on the show.

442
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:47,400
No need.

443
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:49,120
You handled that field discretion

444
00:21:49,120 --> 00:21:50,280
extremely well.

445
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,840
I had no other choice.

446
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:55,040
They were tired of Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui.

447
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:56,640
They asked for Da Jiao Zan.

448
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:57,680
Anything else?

449
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:00,400
Since Da Jiao Zan did so well,

450
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,280
could we bring Yi Qing'e

451
00:22:02,840 --> 00:22:03,880
back to the trainee class?

452
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:04,880
Let's seize the chance

453
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:06,160
and stage Yang Pai Feng next.

454
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:10,000
What if I say no?

455
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:14,760
I'll still stand by my idea.

456
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:16,160
Please, Troupe Leader,

457
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,560
report my idea to the higher-ups.

458
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:21,000
Then report it yourself.

459
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,600
The leaders want a word anyway.

460
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:24,720
Troupe Leader.

461
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:25,760
Troupe Leader.

462
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:27,280
Deputy Troupe Leader.

463
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:30,000
I can't do this anymore.

464
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,500
I can't be the class teacher anymore.

465
00:22:31,760 --> 00:22:32,920
What happened now?

466
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:35,400
Since the kids came back
from the village,

467
00:22:35,920 --> 00:22:37,720
they've been so negative and passive.

468
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:39,560
They won't listen to me

469
00:22:39,920 --> 00:22:41,160
or train properly.

470
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,400
Especially the girls.

471
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:44,880
Their moods are all over the place.

472
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,080
For example, right now,

473
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:49,400
the girls all say
they're on their period.

474
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:50,240
None of them

475
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:51,400
is training.

476
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:52,720
What to do?

477
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:54,720
From now on,

478
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:56,920
you can go straight
to Troupe Leader Zhu.

479
00:22:57,840 --> 00:23:00,960
It's no longer my call.

480
00:23:01,330 --> 00:23:02,320
Wait.

481
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:04,440
What do you mean

482
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:05,520
by that?

483
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:10,000
I won't be your troupe leader soon.

484
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:12,040
Then who will?

485
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:13,680
Once the transfer order comes, I'm gone.

486
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:16,200
The troupe needs an insider
as the leader.

487
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:18,600
I'll be the Director
of the Material Bureau.

488
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,280
I can really understand it.

489
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:29,880
After seeing Yi Qing'e in Da Jiao Zan,

490
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:31,200
you can't accept it.

491
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,200
Comparing yourself to her is rough.

492
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,160
But in my opinion,

493
00:23:37,920 --> 00:23:39,600
to make it in opera,

494
00:23:39,840 --> 00:23:41,000
there are only two ways.

495
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,040
First,

496
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,800
you're born with the gift.

497
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:46,480
Second,

498
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,000
it takes hard work.

499
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,840
Yi Qing'e's skills

500
00:23:50,840 --> 00:23:52,400
didn't fall from the sky.

501
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:53,800
Right?

502
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:56,560
She didn't get there overnight.

503
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:57,920
It came from hard training.

504
00:23:58,520 --> 00:24:00,360
Now, you see the gap.

505
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:01,720
Train hard,

506
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,120
and you can pass her.

507
00:24:03,120 --> 00:24:05,120
We do train hard.

508
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:06,360
Don't jump in.

509
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:09,880
If you only blame others,

510
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:12,360
the gap will only

511
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:13,720
keep growing.

512
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:16,840
We always do vocal drills and tumbling

513
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:18,080
in the morning

514
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,760
and weapon work in the afternoon.

515
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,760
Which of us doesn't have
better conditions?

516
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:25,040
Why end up worse than a kitchen maid?

517
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:27,640
We've suffered for so many years.

518
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:29,200
What have we learned in the end?

519
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,520
Nonsense.

520
00:24:30,826 --> 00:24:32,640
You've learned acting
and life in the troupe.

521
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:33,680
That's just nonsense.

522
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:36,520
I'm more anxious than any of you.

523
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:38,480
I wish all you kids

524
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:39,920
could get onstage right now

525
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:41,200
and play the lead.

526
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,920
I wish you could carry our troupe.

527
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:45,440
But can you?

528
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:47,640
Our troupe

529
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,920
has ended up like this today.

530
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:52,480
Are you sure you're not part
of the reason?

531
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,240
When we run into problems,

532
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:56,080
we have to solve them, right?

533
00:24:56,760 --> 00:24:59,560
Can you look at yourselves for once?

534
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:02,360
Fine. I do have a problem.

535
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:04,840
I request a transfer to the kitchen.

536
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:06,440
That's where I'll learn real skills.

537
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,880
I also request a transfer.

538
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:08,920
- Me too.
- Me too.

539
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:10,440
- I want to go too.
- Me too.

540
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:11,280
Fine.

541
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:12,800
No need to transfer.

542
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:16,280
Tomorrow, the trainee class
will become the cooking squad.

543
00:25:16,720 --> 00:25:18,280
You can all cook in the kitchen.

544
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:26,280
What?

545
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:27,680
What is he doing?

546
00:25:27,780 --> 00:25:29,160
- Is he threatening us?
- Exactly.

547
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:30,400
Why so worked up?

548
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:31,240
Exactly.

549
00:26:02,720 --> 00:26:04,200
How about spear fighting?

550
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:06,200
Not good.

551
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,040
No.

552
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:09,193
Then the broadsword routine?

553
00:26:09,390 --> 00:26:10,280
Still no.

554
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:11,200
Still no?

555
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,160
Then fist fighting?

556
00:26:12,480 --> 00:26:13,600
Even worse.

557
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:16,240
Whose green pants are these?

558
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:18,480
Forget green pants.

559
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:20,640
Let's do staff fighting.

560
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:21,480
Staff fighting?

561
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:25,200
What do you think of staff fighting?

562
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:32,240
Get out.

563
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:36,600
Idiot!

564
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:10,800
Why does Yi Qing'e look so pretty?

565
00:27:11,280 --> 00:27:13,600
Prettier than the poster girls.

566
00:27:16,240 --> 00:27:18,960
The old guys did her makeup well.

567
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:20,240
Exactly, exactly.

568
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:21,120
Exactly.

569
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:21,960
Still awake?

570
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:23,040
I can't fall asleep.

571
00:27:23,220 --> 00:27:24,770
- Let's chat.
- You're still up?

572
00:27:25,480 --> 00:27:27,040
She looks good even without makeup.

573
00:27:28,040 --> 00:27:29,280
Have you noticed?

574
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:31,680
Yi Qing'e got way prettier.

575
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:34,440
You've been watching closely.

576
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:35,280
Exactly.

577
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,080
She was such a goof as a kid.

578
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:39,360
Who knew she'd grow up so pretty?

579
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,480
You little rascal.

580
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:43,440
She's getting prettier.

581
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:45,000
How many have you even seen?

582
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:46,880
Let me finish.

583
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:47,720
I'm telling you.

584
00:27:48,040 --> 00:27:49,600
When a girl is little,

585
00:27:50,160 --> 00:27:51,600
she shouldn't be too pretty.

586
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:52,440
Right.

587
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:55,080
What time is it? Let us sleep.

588
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:57,400
So noisy. How long will this go on?

589
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:59,480
So annoying. Can you shut up?

590
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:00,920
We have to get up early tomorrow.

591
00:28:00,920 --> 00:28:02,760
- Get out.
- What's wrong with you?

592
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:04,480
- Nuts.
- Just chatting.

593
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:06,160
You can sleep. What's the problem?

594
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:07,000
Exactly.

595
00:28:07,280 --> 00:28:09,120
- Let's find Yi Qing'e. Okay?
- Stop.

596
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:10,320
Those two are the ugliest.

597
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:11,170
Come on.

598
00:28:11,170 --> 00:28:12,160
Hurry up.

599
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:14,120
- The uglier one yells louder.
- Go.

600
00:29:11,473 --> 00:29:12,400
What are you two doing?

601
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:13,960
You nearly scared me to death!

602
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:15,240
I...

603
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:16,680
He wanted to watch you train.

604
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,520
Cut it out.

605
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:18,560
No.

606
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:19,840
I...

607
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:21,000
Don't listen to his nonsense.

608
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,080
I'm hungry.

609
00:29:22,560 --> 00:29:23,880
I came to find two Mo to eat.

610
00:29:27,840 --> 00:29:28,760
Where did she go?

611
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:37,440
Aren't you hungry?

612
00:30:05,620 --> 00:30:06,480
Nice.

613
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,320
She gave me two Mo.

614
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:08,560
Share one with me.

615
00:30:08,560 --> 00:30:10,000
Share? She gave them to me.

616
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:10,840
She gave them to me.

617
00:30:22,760 --> 00:30:24,880
Gross. What a faker.

618
00:30:33,880 --> 00:30:35,920
Yang Paifeng, give me a bigger scoop.

619
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:45,880
Give me the ladle. I'll do it.

620
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:50,560
Are you deaf? I said, "Give it to me."

621
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:51,640
What are you doing?

622
00:30:52,520 --> 00:30:53,480
She's grossing me out.

623
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:56,000
What's wrong with you?

624
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:57,440
Chu Jiahe,

625
00:30:58,200 --> 00:30:59,680
she just sang Da Jiao Zan.

626
00:31:00,200 --> 00:31:01,720
Is it because you can't?

627
00:31:03,040 --> 00:31:04,280
Don't take it out on her.

628
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:05,760
What's it to you?

629
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:07,160
Mind your own business.

630
00:31:07,880 --> 00:31:09,080
Bullying people is wrong.

631
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:12,160
Who is she to you anyway?

632
00:31:12,160 --> 00:31:13,240
You care about her, huh?

633
00:31:13,560 --> 00:31:15,480
In that case,
why not just take her home?

634
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:16,400
What's wrong with you?

635
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:18,080
You must be looking for trouble.

636
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:20,253
Don't you have better things to do?

637
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:21,990
Who told you to serve me?

638
00:31:21,990 --> 00:31:22,920
What are you doing?

639
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:24,720
- She grosses me out.
- Have you no shame?

640
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:25,880
- What?
- Apologize to her.

641
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:26,920
Apologize.

642
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:28,475
- Don't leave. Apologize now.
- Let go.

643
00:31:28,486 --> 00:31:29,240
Let go of me.

644
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:30,600
Let go.

645
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:31,440
What's wrong?

646
00:31:31,760 --> 00:31:32,760
Why is she leaving?

647
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,280
- Come back.
- What a coward.

648
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:36,960
Don't go. Stop right there.

649
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:37,800
What happened?

650
00:31:38,200 --> 00:31:39,240
The kid brought her food.

651
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:41,720
She called her dirty
and dumped it on her.

652
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:44,640
You've got way too much nerve.

653
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:45,480
Picking on the kid.

654
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:48,520
Stop banging, all of you.

655
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:50,720
Stop it.

656
00:31:52,200 --> 00:31:54,000
Master Song, where are we going?

657
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:56,080
To get answers from Director Huang. Go.

658
00:31:56,600 --> 00:31:57,760
I'm fine.

659
00:31:58,270 --> 00:31:59,160
How is this fine?

660
00:31:59,160 --> 00:32:00,720
You did nothing wrong. Why be scared?

661
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,840
Don't worry about me, Master Song.

662
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,200
I'm not just worried about you.

663
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:05,120
Look at the mess.

664
00:32:05,120 --> 00:32:06,440
It makes the kitchen look bad.

665
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:07,520
How can we work now?

666
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:08,360
Let's go.

667
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:14,400
The handover files are all here.

668
00:32:15,280 --> 00:32:17,560
I'll pass them to you in advance.

669
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:18,800
Okay.

670
00:32:21,720 --> 00:32:23,080
Leave them with me. Don't worry.

671
00:32:23,660 --> 00:32:25,420
(Files)

672
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:28,120
Since the leadership has spoken to you,

673
00:32:28,120 --> 00:32:29,760
it's basically settled now.

674
00:32:29,760 --> 00:32:30,640
Right, right.

675
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:33,400
No rush.

676
00:32:33,553 --> 00:32:35,800
Once the transfer order comes,
you'll have the position.

677
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:38,920
Troupe Leader,

678
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:41,000
your place in my heart won't change.

679
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,000
- What place?
- Troupe Leader.

680
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:44,880
Right at the center.

681
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:45,720
Troupe Leader.

682
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:48,560
Come here. Stand right there.

683
00:32:48,920 --> 00:32:49,840
Look at this.

684
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:50,960
What happened?

685
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:52,600
Chu Jiahe from the trainee class

686
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:54,106
grabbed the ladle for no reason

687
00:32:54,117 --> 00:32:55,450
and spilled food all over the kid.

688
00:32:55,800 --> 00:32:57,000
For no reason?

689
00:32:58,280 --> 00:33:00,160
No one hates someone for no reason.

690
00:33:00,979 --> 00:33:01,880
So many people saw it.

691
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:03,360
Go ask around, then.

692
00:33:04,880 --> 00:33:06,000
I've handed this over.

693
00:33:06,560 --> 00:33:07,680
You look into it.

694
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:12,000
Troupe Leader, you can't just leave.

695
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,280
Master Song.

696
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:16,920
Take the kid to wash up first.

697
00:33:17,113 --> 00:33:18,180
I'll find out what happened

698
00:33:18,180 --> 00:33:19,160
and decide what to do.

699
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,720
No. Handle this right now.

700
00:33:20,731 --> 00:33:22,000
If not, dinner can't even start.

701
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:23,080
Why can't it start?

702
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:24,200
This is just too much.

703
00:33:36,040 --> 00:33:36,880
Qing'e,

704
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:39,400
I apologize
on behalf of Chu Jiahe first.

705
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:40,920
Will that do?

706
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:46,080
I'm fine.

707
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:48,040
Well...

708
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:51,440
Hey, this kid...

709
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:11,240
I'll handle this.

710
00:34:24,040 --> 00:34:25,440
Master, did you call me?

711
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:30,840
You've been back for days.

712
00:34:31,920 --> 00:34:33,520
You should've calmed down by now.

713
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:35,880
That night in Da Jiao Zan,

714
00:34:36,360 --> 00:34:37,480
how do you think you did?

715
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,600
I don't know.

716
00:34:41,240 --> 00:34:43,800
I'd give you a sixty. Barely passing.

717
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:47,800
So many cheered that night,

718
00:34:48,200 --> 00:34:50,920
because they hadn't seen
old opera in years.

719
00:34:51,720 --> 00:34:53,160
To be honest, that night,

720
00:34:53,160 --> 00:34:54,680
your eyes weren't bright enough.

721
00:34:55,640 --> 00:34:56,840
They lacked a spark.

722
00:34:59,120 --> 00:34:59,960
Look.

723
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:02,280
When a Dan role is onstage,

724
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:03,840
all the technique

725
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:06,160
ends up in those two eyes.

726
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:10,520
If the eyes are dull,
the role has no soul.

727
00:35:11,160 --> 00:35:12,160
When the eyes shine,

728
00:35:12,680 --> 00:35:14,680
the performance comes alive.

729
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:28,120
Go and light two sticks of incense.

730
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:30,120
Work on your eyes properly.

731
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:30,960
All right.

732
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:32,120
Go on.

733
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:08,720
Who is it?

734
00:36:09,080 --> 00:36:10,680
It's me, Mi Lan.

735
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:21,560
What's wrong, Mi Lan?

736
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:22,960
What happened to you?

737
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:24,680
Nothing.

738
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:26,080
What did Liao do to you?

739
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:31,040
Is what they said true?

740
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:32,960
What did they say?

741
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:35,120
They said that Chef Liao

742
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:36,000
forced himself on you.

743
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:41,520
Is it true?

744
00:36:42,520 --> 00:36:43,440
Say something.

745
00:36:45,600 --> 00:36:46,440
Tell me.

746
00:36:46,766 --> 00:36:47,952
I don't want to talk about it.

747
00:36:48,160 --> 00:36:49,640
You need to tell me now.

748
00:36:53,160 --> 00:36:54,000
Come on, tell me.

749
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:01,720
He pinned me to the bed and tried

750
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:03,400
to undo my belt.

751
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:04,600
And then?

752
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:07,800
Then Master Song rushed in and hit him.

753
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,046
Did he get your belt open?

754
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:13,779
No. It was tied in a tight knot.

755
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:16,360
Is that all he did to you?

756
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:24,160
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

757
00:37:24,626 --> 00:37:25,720
Master Song told me not to.

758
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:27,120
He said it would hurt me.

759
00:37:27,480 --> 00:37:28,600
Who else knows about this?

760
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:30,000
Only Master Song.

761
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,720
Then how did Chu Jiahe know?

762
00:37:32,440 --> 00:37:34,040
She said you were taken advantage of.

763
00:37:40,440 --> 00:37:41,360
Mi Lan,

764
00:37:42,760 --> 00:37:44,480
was I really taken advantage of?

765
00:37:46,600 --> 00:37:47,880
Master Song saved you.

766
00:37:49,360 --> 00:37:50,880
Then Chu Jiahe ruined your name.

767
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:55,280
Let's go find them.

768
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:57,000
I'm not going.

769
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:58,440
I'm here. What are you scared of?

770
00:37:58,440 --> 00:37:59,480
I'm scared of everything.

771
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:02,600
What's wrong with you?

772
00:38:03,520 --> 00:38:05,640
If you don't clear this up with her,

773
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:07,600
life will only get harder for you.

774
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:08,440
Do you get that?

775
00:38:09,360 --> 00:38:10,760
You weren't like this as a kid.

776
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:13,560
You caught snakes and fought Er Laizi.

777
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:14,800
What happened to you?

778
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:16,600
You've turned into a lamb.

779
00:38:16,600 --> 00:38:18,000
Anyone can push you around, right?

780
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:23,760
Silly.

781
00:38:24,720 --> 00:38:25,560
I'm not silly.

782
00:38:28,520 --> 00:38:29,360
Look at them.

783
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:32,280
Each one looks more real than the last.

784
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:36,640
They need a master to train them.

785
00:38:37,400 --> 00:38:38,280
Chu Jiahe.

786
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:41,720
Ms. Mi Lan.

787
00:38:42,092 --> 00:38:43,205
I need to ask you something.

788
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:45,040
Ms. Mi Lan, what is it?

789
00:38:46,240 --> 00:38:47,080
Come with me.

790
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:48,760
What's wrong?

791
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:11,600
Why did you bring me here?

792
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:14,480
Come over here.

793
00:39:16,640 --> 00:39:17,480
Come here.

794
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:23,520
Let go of me.

795
00:39:25,680 --> 00:39:27,120
Let go.

796
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:30,200
Feeling guilty?

797
00:39:31,519 --> 00:39:32,960
What do I have to feel guilty about?

798
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:35,646
Did you start that rumor of Yi Qing'e

799
00:39:35,657 --> 00:39:37,120
being taken advantage of by Liao?

800
00:39:37,520 --> 00:39:38,360
It's not a rumor.

801
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:39,840
You saw it?

802
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:41,240
Yes.

803
00:39:41,560 --> 00:39:43,080
What's your relationship with Liao?

804
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:44,406
Did he let you watch

805
00:39:44,417 --> 00:39:45,840
how he took advantage of Yi Qing'e?

806
00:39:46,160 --> 00:39:48,040
Tomorrow, I'll tell the whole troupe

807
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:50,440
that when Liao took advantage
of Yi Qing'e,

808
00:39:50,440 --> 00:39:52,040
you were in it with him.

809
00:39:53,040 --> 00:39:54,353
What did Yi Qing'e ever do to you?

810
00:39:55,253 --> 00:39:56,533
Why did you treat her like this?

811
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:00,000
Answer me.

812
00:40:04,600 --> 00:40:06,280
I taught you stagecraft.

813
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:09,000
Not these dirty tricks offstage.

814
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:11,600
As an opera performer,

815
00:40:11,693 --> 00:40:12,880
if you can't even be decent,

816
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:14,360
how can you play any role?

817
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:17,640
She suddenly made it.

818
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:19,520
It's hard for me too.

819
00:40:20,160 --> 00:40:21,760
But I accept my fate.

820
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:24,560
If you can't stand her doing well,

821
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:26,960
work harder onstage.

822
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:28,560
Compete with her up there.

823
00:40:29,120 --> 00:40:30,120
Don't do it offstage

824
00:40:30,120 --> 00:40:31,560
with such low tactics.

825
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:34,560
I'm making this clear today.

826
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:37,520
If you ever hurt Yi Qing'e again,

827
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:40,520
I'll expose you to the whole troupe.

828
00:40:41,686 --> 00:40:42,960
Try me if you don't believe it.

829
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:46,880
Qing'e.

830
00:40:48,360 --> 00:40:49,200
Qing'e.

831
00:41:00,440 --> 00:41:01,440
Apologize to Yi Qing'e.

832
00:41:04,240 --> 00:41:05,080
Apologize.

833
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:07,880
Get back here.

834
00:41:16,880 --> 00:41:18,560
Don't chase her, Mi Lan.

835
00:41:21,240 --> 00:41:22,520
I'll go get you something.

836
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:24,200
Wait here for me.

837
00:41:26,680 --> 00:41:29,120
Jiahe, what did Ms. Mi Lan say?

838
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:31,380
- What?
- Stop bugging me.

839
00:41:31,380 --> 00:41:32,480
Get back to practice.

840
00:41:41,720 --> 00:41:43,240
These practice outfits are brand-new.

841
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:44,920
I won't need them anymore.

842
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:45,920
Take them and wear them.

843
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:47,400
This scarf is for you.

844
00:41:48,200 --> 00:41:49,480
In my room,

845
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:50,840
there are lots of things.

846
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:52,240
If you can use any of them,

847
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:53,240
go and take them.

848
00:41:55,880 --> 00:41:57,720
This Xinhua Dictionary is for you.

849
00:41:58,100 --> 00:42:00,280
(Xinhua Dictionary)
To be the lead, you have to study.

850
00:42:03,160 --> 00:42:04,280
I'm leaving tomorrow.

851
00:42:06,200 --> 00:42:07,120
Where are you going?

852
00:42:08,080 --> 00:42:08,920
To the south.

853
00:42:09,200 --> 00:42:10,040
What for?

854
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:11,640
To get married.

855
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:13,640
You're giving up opera?

856
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:17,360
In this line of work, there's no choice.

857
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:19,680
There's only one leading role.

858
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:21,760
Once you're the lead,

859
00:42:22,280 --> 00:42:23,720
attention naturally follows.

860
00:42:24,640 --> 00:42:26,200
You're still a sapling,

861
00:42:26,600 --> 00:42:27,960
yet you've already drawn the storm.

862
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:30,760
As for stage skills,

863
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:31,920
you've only learned half.

864
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:34,640
You need to keep studying hard.

865
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:37,400
As for life offstage,

866
00:42:38,846 --> 00:42:40,852
I doubt Master Gou and the others
can teach you.

867
00:42:42,720 --> 00:42:44,880
Figure it out yourself.

868
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:50,040
I'm leaving early tomorrow.

869
00:42:50,520 --> 00:42:51,600
I haven't told anyone.

870
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:53,880
Come see me off.

871
00:43:00,660 --> 00:43:04,660
(Xinhua Dictionary)

872
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

873
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:11,640
You've had it hard all these years.

874
00:43:12,320 --> 00:43:14,760
The troupe is back with pros.

875
00:43:15,240 --> 00:43:16,530
Let's do Yang Men Nyu Jiang.

876
00:43:16,690 --> 00:43:18,700
The girls in our trainee class

877
00:43:18,830 --> 00:43:19,810
can all go onstage.

878
00:43:19,820 --> 00:43:21,090
For Mu Guiying,

879
00:43:21,310 --> 00:43:22,560
Yi Qing'e is the first choice.

880
00:43:22,750 --> 00:43:23,970
Chu Jiahe is second.

881
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:25,630
Roles aren't about importance.

882
00:43:26,120 --> 00:43:27,440
For the opera armor,

883
00:43:27,440 --> 00:43:28,680
we still need 14 sets.

884
00:43:29,200 --> 00:43:31,400
If Chu Jiahe plays Mu Guiying,

885
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:32,680
will the costume issue be solved?

886
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

887
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

888
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

889
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

890
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

891
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

892
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

893
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

894
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

895
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

896
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

897
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

898
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

899
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

900
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

901
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

902
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

903
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

904
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

905
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

906
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪

